spans.text: the hours which lead each fleeting year
calm reflection the sad moral teach , That bliss below evades our eager reach
like hers may soon those beauties
like hers may soon those beauties
The thoughtful parent dropped the silent tear

thee just expiring lie , Pale thy cold lip , half closed thy languid eye , Thy guardian Innocence beside thee stands , And patient Faith uplifts her holy hands , Teach thee with smiles to meet the stroke of Death , Calm all thy pangs , and ease thy struggling breath
with smiles to meet the stroke of Death ,
the constant Amaranthus bloom , And wings of Zephyrs
spread the cloud : his torch extinct , he flies , And veils with saffron robe his streaming eyes
his torch extinct , he flies , And veils with saffron robe his streaming eyes
plaintive sounds of mortal grief below Reach the blessed seats , and waft our tender woe ,
